<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,1742,2093]" lastBlockId="12.[136,1452,158,329]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,492,2030,2056]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Distribution and ecology:</emphasis>
—The species occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[765,853,2030,2056]" name="Mexico" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[864,956,2031,2057]" name="Panama" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[966,1079,2030,2056]" name="Colombia" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1090,1208,2030,2056]" name="Venezuela" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1218,1322,2031,2057]" name="Paraguay" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1376,1447,2030,2056]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, where it can be found in the Central-West (
<collectingRegion box="[649,687,2066,2092]" country="Brazil" name="DF" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">DF</collectingRegion>
, GO), Northeast (
<collectingRegion box="[897,940,2066,2092]" country="Brazil" name="BA" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">BA</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[955,993,2066,2092]" country="Brazil" name="CE" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">CE</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1009,1045,2066,2092]" country="Brazil" name="PA" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">PA</collectingRegion>
, PE), Southeast (
<collectingRegion box="[1248,1297,2066,2092]" country="Brazil" name="MG" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">MG</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1312,1344,2067,2093]" country="Brazil" name="RJ" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">RJ</collectingRegion>
, SP) and South (
<collectingRegion box="[216,254,158,184]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">PR</collectingRegion>
, SC) associated with the domains of Caatinga, Cerrado and Atlantic Rainforest (BFG 2018; INCT - Virtual Herbarium of Flora and Fungi). In the study area, it was collected on the outcrop plateau at 
<quantity box="[1162,1241,194,220]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.197" pageId="12" pageNumber="29" unit="m" value="1197.0">1197m</quantity>
, in litolic soil.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,158,329]" box="[189,833,230,256]" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,230,256]" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Registered with flowers and fruits in April.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[136,1452,158,329]" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ker Gawler" authorityYear="1820" box="[189,410,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Crotalaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="12" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitellina">
<emphasis box="[189,410,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="29">Crotalaria vitellina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized, mainly, by the subshrub habit, trifoliolate and palmate leaves, raceme inflorescence and yellow corolla. In the study area, it was the only one to present inflated legume.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
